Highlights: Michigan’s seasonally adjusted unemployment rate remained 4.5 percent in June. The jobless rate is 0.1 percentage points above the rate marked in June 2017.
Michigan’s seasonally adjusted unemployment rate inched down to 4.3 percent in July. The jobless rate is 0.2 percentage points below the rate marked in July 2017.
